-- BP to Provide First $2.5 Billion for Alberta Oil-Sands Project, FT Says
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-11-30T05:51:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/bp-to-provide-first-2-5-billion-for-oil-sands-project-ft-says.html
BP Plc , which is partnering Husky
Energy Inc. in the development of oil sands in northern Alberta,
Canada, will provide the first $2.5 billion of expenditure on
the project, though it has only a 50 percent share of the
venture, the Financial Times reported, without saying where it
got that information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alan Purkiss  in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge in London at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 